OL,6,FEarly 20th century - Ongoing
OL,7,FmaintenanceRoutine repairs continue as
OL,8,Fthe narrow Victorian bridge adapts to
OL,9,Fheavier vehicles.
OL,11,F1973-1975 - Major
OL,12,FreinforcementExtensive structural
OL,13,Fworks on the piers and deck preserve
OL,14,Fthe bridge for continued use.
OL,16,F1970s - Weight restrictions
OL,17,FintroducedA three-tonne limit is
OL,18,Fimposed to protect the fragile
OL,19,Fstructure - pedestrians and cyclists
OL,20,Fbecome the primary users.
